Masumoto &amp; Okajima
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,847,1016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">
This genus was erected for two Southeast Asian species together with a key to distinguish them, and with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masumoto &amp; Okajima" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Trachynotothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">T. striatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus box="[282,330,885,909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">type</typeStatus>
species. The species have a strongly enlarged metathoracic furca (
<figureCitation box="[1123,1211,884,909]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–39" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[208,1384,193,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[208,1384,193,1922]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 31–39. Head and pronotum of Trichromothrips genus-group species. (31) Laplothrips bicolor. (32) Yoshinothrips pasekamui. (33) Octothrips bhatti. (34) Trachynotothrips striatus. (35) Trichromothrips falcus. (36) T. elegans. (37) T. crispator. (38) T. trifasciatus. (39) T. indicus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2618157/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
), similar to that of Dendrothripinae and some members of Panchaetothripinae. This structure may be associated with thrips jumping activity rather than indicating any phylogenetic relationship (
<bibRefCitation author="Masumoto, M. &amp; Okajima, S." box="[842,1167,956,981]" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" pagination="53 - 64" refId="ref7312" refString="Masumoto, M. &amp; Okajima, S. (2005) A remarkable new genus of Thripinae (Thysanoptera, Thripidae) with enlarged metathoracic furca, from Southeast Asia. Zootaxa, 1048 (1), 53 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1082.1.1" type="journal article" year="2005">Masumoto &amp; Okajima 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Two 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Masumoto &amp; Okajima" authorityYear="2005" box="[1243,1436,956,981]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Trachynotothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1243,1436,956,981]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">Trachynotothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are here recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[502,569,991,1016]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="80">China</collectingCountry>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
